@node smp "Sample"
                                 @{b}Sample@{ub}
                              ==============

sample installing

1.run eSetup

2.switch on eInstaller AutoMate to ON [O] (needed to perform)

3.click on disk icon at Set Install Config
3.leave Drawer as PROGDIR
3.at File inbox type eInstaller (do not type in the extension ) 
3.& click ok if you are happy with name.

4.click on disk icon at Device/Dir
4.select eInstaller drawer & click on ASL ok button if you are happy with it.
4.do not touch Drawer=PROGDIR:eInstaller-v1 for now.


3.should show PROGDIR:eInstaller

4.should show PROGDIR:eInstaller-v1/


5.click on go right arrow button to start generating a eInstaller.config file

6.now check where you run if eSetup created a eInstaller.config file



then run eInstaller were you have run eSetup 

1.switch on eInstaller to ON [O] (needed to perform)

2.click on disk icon at Get .Config 
2.select eInstaller.Config filename

3.click on disk icon at Install To
3.& click on Valumes select ram: (not ram disk: edit to just ram:t/)

2.should show PROGDIR:eInstaller.config (location of .Config file)

3.should show Ram:T/ (Install To)

then click Go arrow button.

thats all


@endnode

@node Install "Installation"
                                 @{b}Installation@{ub}
                                ==============


open eInstaller-v1/68020 or 68040 version 
&
copy eInstaller/eSetup to were ever you want in your hard disk.


!copy Paboot to sys:c/ (not realy needed just are about window pops up)
     when you click on about icon on gui.
     but 
     will work without is well.

@endnode



@node usage "usage"

This Project started just after Ziprecover v2 if you did install ZipRecover then 
you now where i got the structure but then again we needed a simple & user friendly
installer & i have created called eInstaller (easy Installer) not finnished yet
but with your help i try to get all those bug mails & try to recompile a better 
user friendly version.


                               @{b}eInstaller@{ub}
                              ==============



eInstaller Installs what ever you have set in Install.Config file.

no need key file or register to use eInstaller/eSetup.
   

                               @{b}eSetup@{ub}
                              ==============

eSetup(we call eInstaller AutoMate)
eSetup Generates Install.Config filename. 

you dont have to type pages to install anymore, eSetup does that for you.



some tips
---------
1.if you want to install library files to sys:libs/ best to make another 
Install.config & name it to libs_Install.Config so you can install'em after
you install main install.config. 
when installing set install To (sys:libs/ or libs:) then click go button.

Features to addon v2
--------------------
1.option to install system files easy'er.
2.prosessor selection.
3.long dir/device names.
4.more user friendly. 
5.unInstalling.
6.auto assign (to user-startup or drawer)
7.& more but you can email any other features not listed here.

tring to compile a User Friendly Installer for amigas by amigans.

Portacall Amiga User Group (PAUG 2004 free software under www.webmem.net)


@endnode

@node Bug "Bug"
                                @{b}Bugs&Notes@{ub}
                              ==============
eInstaller / eSetup v1
----------------------

not tested on all amigas yet we now it works on a1200 +020/040/060 
if you can not get this tool running on you amiga please e-mail with your sys setup



1.sometimes progress bar/filenames  wont display ?
>when first in first out file size is smaller than next file then progress 
 bar calculates 0 to 0 makes -file size until last file size.
>fixed?. not fixed yet but will be in v2 & should work most time.


2.wont create drawer?
> check .Config file & see if #DRW-LIST is empty
>if it's empty copy first line just after #FILES-LIST until drawer / charecter.
>example 
        
        DRW-LIST
to>     ram:eInstaller-v1/    (copy & past root drawer here if empty)
                              (!not ram:eInstaller/68020/)
                              (just the root/first drawer)
        #FILES-LIST 
from>   ram:einstaller-v1/68020/eSetup (from here)

>will be fixed next version


3. .info of first drawer not installed you can edit your .Config file to fix that.
>  example
          add a line in #FILES-LIST
                PROGDIR:eInstaller.info

>thats fixed now but if you get this problem e-mail at www.webmem.net
>also you can edit your .Config file & fixit. (i will rework on this v2) 


its not realy hard to use eInstaller/eSetup if you work on .Config file a bit. 

           
!no blank spaces in device names like ram disk: instead use ram:
